        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 2:07AM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 207 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Stanley, or 8 miles south of Newburgh, moving east at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Owensboro, Rockport, Grandview, Knottsville, Stanley, and Eureka.

This includes Audubon Parkway between Mile Markers 21 and 23.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
